				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, using CHR-RAM in place of CHR-ROM in any mapper with CHR bankswitching more or less presupposes the emulator iNES 2 support, except for 1 or 2 special cases of mappers previously known to have 32k CHR-RAM. Otherwise there's no way to specify how much CHR-RAM you need.<br /><br />I think you'll find a lot of older emulators will not do CHR-RAM for arbitrary mappers, even the &quot;0 CHR-ROM = normally assume 8k CHR-RAM&quot; iNES 1 level support is pretty spotty from what I've seen.<br /><br />If the emulator supports iNES 2 it really probably should let you do it for all mappers.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

